  "prompt": "What are the best romantic comedy movies?",
  "response": "There are many fantastic romantic comedies that have become beloved classics or modern favorites. Here are some of the best:\n\n1. **When Harry Met Sally... (1989)** - A defining film of the genre that explores the question of whether men and women can ever just be friends.\n\n2. **Notting Hill (1999)** - A charming story about a bookstore owner and a famous actress who fall in love despite their disparate lifestyles.\n\n3. **10 Things I Hate About You (1999)** - A modern adaptation of Shakespeare's \"The Taming of the Shrew,\" featuring witty dialogue and a memorable performance by Heath Ledger.\n\n4. **Crazy, Stupid, Love (2011)** - A multi-layered story about love and relationships, with a stellar ensemble cast including Steve Carell, Ryan Gosling, and Emma Stone.\n\n5. **The Proposal (2009)** - A fun and lighthearted story about a Canadian author who pretends to be engaged to her assistant to avoid deportation, starring Sandra Bullock and Ryan Reynolds.\n\n6. **Bridget Jones's Diary (2001)** - Based on the popular book, this film chronicles the ups and downs of Bridget, played by Ren\u00e9e Zellweger, as she navigates love and self-discovery.\n\n7. **Love Actually (2003)** - A holiday-themed ensemble film that intertwines several romantic storylines, showcasing love in various forms.\n\n8. **The 40-Year-Old Virgin (2005)** - A hilarious take on relationships, focusing on a middle-aged man who is still a virgin and his friends' attempts to help him find love.\n\n9. **500 Days of Summer (2009)** - A non-linear narrative that explores the complexities of love and relationships between two young people, starring Joseph Gordon-Levitt and Zooey Deschanel.\n\n10. **To All the Boys I've Loved Before (2018)** - A charming Netflix adaptation of the popular young adult novel about a girl's secret love letters that are accidentally sent out.\n\nThese films offer a great mix of humor, romance, and often memorable performances. Whether you enjoy classics or newer releases, there's plenty to choose from in the romantic comedy genre!",
